-- Polish Treasury Minister Rules Out Lotos Bid by PKN Orlen, Parkiet Reports
-- Dorota Bartyzel
-- 2010-09-07T05:46:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-07/polish-treasury-minister-rules-out-lotos-bid-by-pkn-orlen-parkiet-reports.html

          
          
             Polish Treasury Minister  Aleksander Grad  ruled out any participation by PKN Orlen SA in bidding for
Grupa Lotos SA, Parkiet reported.  
 Grad also denied that the ministry has considered the
possibility of Polskie Gornictwo Naftowe i Gazownictwo bidding
for Lotos, the newspaper said.  
 Orlen is Poland’s largest oil refiner, Lotos the second-
largest and Polskie Gornictwo Naftowe i Gazownictwo SA is the
country’s gas monopoly.  
